FEEL THE DIFFERENCE OF MEMORY CARE AT CHARTER SENIOR LIVING of Linden

Are you beginning to notice signs of dementia in your loved one? Often, this is simply a natural part of aging. If this is the case and you’re unsure where to turn to for help, let Charter Senior Living of Linden be your guide.

Memory Care takes patience, courage, and above all else, compassion. We practice all three and go even further To Enhance the Human Spirit as dementia progresses.

Charter Senior Living of Linden located in Linden, MIchigan allows your family and your loved one with memory loss to experience a safe, structured environment with set routines and a higher level of specialized care and programming. Our dementia care plan is designed to lower stress and increase dignity for those living with Alzheimer’s, other forms of dementia, and memory problems.

With a dedicated and highly trained care team, residents are met with anytime dining and assistance with daily responsibilities that you’d typically find at an Assisted Living facility. Care includes:

  • Dressing
  • Bathing
  • Grooming
  • Other essential activities of daily living (ADLs)

Our staff is also specially trained to deal with the unique issues that often arise due to dementia or Alzheimer's. They check in with residents more frequently to build a sense of familiarity and provide extra support in Memory Care services to help them navigate their day.

FLOURISH℠ MEMORY CARE

We believe in letting the good things grow. With our unique, research-based approach to Memory Care, Flourish℠ programming promises to cultivate love, nurture purpose, and fiercely preserve the dignity of those who are facing memory loss. Guided by this philosophy, residents at Charter Senior Living of Linden benefit from a comprehensive program led by team members specially trained in Alzheimer’s and dementia care, provided only by Charter Senior Living. Flourish℠ allows us to practice compassion and advocate courageously for your loved one. Experience the difference of our care, today.[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row column_structure="1_2,1_2" use_custom_gutter="on" gutter_width="1" make_equal="on" custom_padding_last_edited="on|phone" module_class="reverse" _builder_version="4.19.5" _module_preset="default" width="100%" max_width="9999px" module_alignment="center" custom_padding="40px||40px|||" custom_padding_tablet="0px||0px||false|false" custom_padding_phone="0px||0px||false|false" global_colors_info="{}" theme_builder_area="post_content"][et_pb_column type="1_2" _builder_version="4.19.5" _module_preset="default" background_color="#edf7f6" custom_padding="5%|5%|5%|5%|true|true" custom_padding_tablet="7%|7%|7%|7%|true|true" custom_padding_phone="10%|10%|10%|10%|true|true" custom_padding_last_edited="on|phone" custom_css_main_element="margin:auto;" global_colors_info="{}" theme_builder_area="post_content"][et_pb_text _builder_version="4.19.5" _module_preset="default" text_line_height="1.9em" header_2_line_height="1.3em" header_2_font_size_tablet="21px" header_2_font_size_phone="18px" header_2_font_size_last_edited="on|phone" global_colors_info="{}" theme_builder_area="post_content"]

MEMORY CARE RESIDENCES + FLOOR PLANS

Welcome to Memory Care residences that are designed for safety and accessibility. Residents feel comfortable in a home that allows them to make the most of each day, and they can customize their surroundings to their needs. Family caregivers find peace of mind knowing that with 24/7 security, their loved one will be free to explore inside and outside their home without the worry of wandering. Someone will always be there to make sure they are safe. Which floor plan makes the most sense for your loved one? Check them out, and take the first step in discovering the difference of our community.[/et_pb_text][et_pb_button DEMENTIA CARE PROGRAMMING ACTIVITIES & SERVICES

FlourishSM goes beyond assisting with daily personal tasks and health care services. Through specialized activities designed specifically for those with cognitive impairment, Charter Senior Living of Linden engages Memory Care residents in ways that make every moment count. To do so, Charter Senior Living of Linden has built an activities calendar based on the foundation of FlourishSM‘s Six Pathways to Supportive Care. With a focus on restoring, enriching, connecting, creating, engaging, and contributing, Memory Care residents are met with uplifting, wellness-focused experiences – and celebrated every step of the way. From hands-on arts and crafts to cooking classes, holiday celebrations, and other exciting opportunities, Memory Care residents at Charter of Linden find many ways to find happiness and flourish.[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section][et_pb_section fb_built="1" custom_padding_last_edited="on|phone" admin_label="First Section" module_id="faqSection" _builder_version="4.17.4" _module_preset="default" custom_padding="0px||0px||true|false" custom_padding_tablet="||0px||false|false" custom_padding_phone="" da_disable_devices="off|off|off" global_colors_info="{}" theme_builder_area="post_content"][et_pb_row use_custom_gutter="on" gutter_width="2" make_equal="on" custom_padding_last_edited="on|phone" _builder_version="4.19.5" _module_preset="default" width="90%" max_width="9999px" custom_padding="40px||80px||false|false" custom_padding_tablet="40px||40px||false|false" custom_padding_phone="40px||40px||false|false" global_colors_info="{}" theme_builder_area="post_content"][et_pb_column type="4_4" _builder_version="4.17.4" _module_preset="default" custom_padding="||||false|false" custom_padding_tablet="||||false|false" custom_padding_phone="" custom_padding_last_edited="on|phone" global_colors_info="{}" theme_builder_area="post_content"][et_pb_text _builder_version="4.19.5" _module_preset="default" header_2_font="|||on|||||" custom_padding="||||true|false" custom_padding_tablet="4%|4%|4%|4%|true|true" custom_padding_last_edited="off|desktop" header_2_font_size_tablet="21px" header_2_font_size_phone="18px" header_2_font_size_last_edited="on|phone" global_colors_info="{}" theme_builder_area="post_content"]

Frequently Asked Questions

[/et_pb_text][et_pb_accordion closed_toggle_background_color="#edf7f6" _builder_version="4.19.5" _module_preset="default" toggle_text_color="#212d65" toggle_font="|700||on|||||" toggle_font_size="26px" toggle_line_height="1.3em" body_line_height="1.9em" width="100%" max_width="9999%" toggle_font_size_tablet="21px" toggle_font_size_phone="18px" toggle_font_size_last_edited="on|phone" global_colors_info="{}" theme_builder_area="post_content"][et_pb_accordion_item title="What is Memory Care for seniors?" open="on" _builder_version="4.19.5" _module_preset="default" global_colors_info="{}" toggle_level="h2" toggle_font="|||on|||||" theme_builder_area="post_content"]

Memory Care is a long-term care plan provided at either a senior living community with other care levels or at a stand-alone Memory Care community.

A person with dementia will reside in a Memory Care community if they are no longer able to live safely at home or need more medical care than what’s provided in-home care from family caregivers or nurses.

At Charter Senior living of Linden, we provide personalized care to every wonderful resident in our Memory Care neighborhood, along with services and amenities that help them thrive.

[/et_pb_accordion_item][et_pb_accordion_item title="Does Your Community Serve Seniors at All Stages of Memory Loss?" _builder_version="4.19.5" _module_preset="default" global_colors_info="{}" toggle_level="h2" toggle_font="|||on|||||" theme_builder_area="post_content" open="off"]

Whether your loved one is in the early or late stages of dementia, our community is equipped to handle it all.

Signs of early-stage dementia include forgetting names, repetition, and struggling to find the right words to describe feelings. Signs of later-stage dementia may include little to no communication, loss of mobility, incontinence, and the inability to eat or dress.

Of course, dementia and Alzheimer’s look different for every family. That’s why we created a unique program in Flourish℠ – to personalize care exactly to your loved one’s needs.

[/et_pb_accordion_item][et_pb_accordion_item title="How can I decide between assisted living and memory care?" _builder_version="4.19.5" _module_preset="default" global_colors_info="{}" toggle_text_color="#212d65" toggle_level="h2" toggle_font="Cormorant Garamond|700|||||||" toggle_font_size_tablet="18px" toggle_font_size_phone="16px" toggle_font_size_last_edited="on|tablet" theme_builder_area="post_content" open="off"]

Assisted Living and Memory Care senior living communities provide many of the same services,  including housing; meals; and help with bathing, grooming and toileting. However, Memory Care communities or neighborhoods specialize in caring for seniors with all stages of Alzheimer’s disease or other forms of dementia. In Memory Care communities, environmental security is a key design feature.

To prevent wandering, many communities are equipped with locked entrances and exits, as well as keypad entries, obscured exits, and doorbells signaling entering and exiting. To avoid injuries from falls, dementia care communities feature designs that minimize confusion. In addition, they offer calming therapies in soothing spaces. This can help reduce agitation and confusion that can lead to aggression or self-injury.

The staff members in dementia care communities are also specially trained in care planning for those living with memory loss. The staff understands how to effectively prevent and manage difficult dementia behaviors. They also understand the balance of encouraging residents to stay as independent as possible while providing the support they need. Many communities, including Charter, have a higher staff-to-resident ratio than Assisted Living, which allows for more one-on-one attention throughout the day.

[/et_pb_accordion_item][et_pb_accordion_item title="What is the cost of memory care?" _builder_version="4.19.5" _module_preset="default" global_colors_info="{}" toggle_text_color="#212d65" toggle_level="h2" toggle_font="Cormorant Garamond||||||||" toggle_font_size_tablet="18px" toggle_font_size_phone="16px" toggle_font_size_last_edited="on|tablet" theme_builder_area="post_content" open="off"]

The higher level of care and supervision in an Alzheimer’s residential care home comes at a price. On average, Assisted Living costs $4,000 a month, and Memory Care adds another $1,000 to $4,000 a month. Costs vary state to state and are impacted by the level of care provided.

Our monthly rates start at $5,900.

[/et_pb_accordion_item][et_pb_accordion_item title="WHAT IS INCLUDED IN ALL-INCLUSIVE MEMORY CARE?" _builder_version="4.19.5" _module_preset="default" global_colors_info="{}" toggle_text_color="#212d65" toggle_level="h2" toggle_font="Cormorant Garamond||||||||" toggle_font_size_tablet="18px" toggle_font_size_phone="16px" toggle_font_size_last_edited="on|tablet" theme_builder_area="post_content" open="off"]Our Memory Care offers all-inclusive care, ensuring that our memory care residents receive the support they need for one all-inclusive monthly fee.[/et_pb_accordion_item][et_pb_accordion_item title="Does Medicare cover memory care?" _builder_version="4.19.5" _module_preset="default" global_colors_info="{}" toggle_text_color="#212d65" toggle_level="h2" toggle_font="Cormorant Garamond|700|||||||" toggle_font_size_tablet="18px" toggle_font_size_phone="16px" toggle_font_size_last_edited="on|tablet" theme_builder_area="post_content" open="off"]

Medicare and Medicare Advantage Plans generally will not pay for room and board or personal care in a Memory Care community. Memory Care will, however, pay for the medical care the facility provides. Veterans benefits typically help cover the cost for eligible Veterans and surviving spouses who are over age 65.

[/et_pb_accordion_item][et_pb_accordion_item title="Is dementia care right for my loved one?" _builder_version="4.19.5" _module_preset="default" body_link_font="||||on||||" body_link_text_color="#212e65" global_colors_info="{}" toggle_text_color="#212d65" toggle_level="h2" toggle_font="Cormorant Garamond|700|||||||" toggle_font_size_tablet="18px" toggle_font_size_phone="16px" toggle_font_size_last_edited="on|tablet" theme_builder_area="post_content" open="off"]

When considering moving your loved one to a senior living community that specializes in dementia care and Alzheimer’s disease, there is much to consider.

  • Are they in the early stage of the disease, or do they need the long-term care provided in nursing homes?
  • Will they have the support they need?
  • Will they be safe, happy and content?

Complete the contact form to find out more about our unique Memory Care programming. Read more about what sets our Alzheimer’s and dementia care apart on our blog.

[/et_pb_accordion_item][et_pb_accordion_item title="How do you get respite care for dementia patients?" _builder_version="4.19.5" _module_preset="default" body_link_font="||||on||||" body_link_text_color="#212e65" global_colors_info="{}" toggle_text_color="#212d65" toggle_level="h2" toggle_font="Cormorant Garamond|700|||||||" toggle_font_size_tablet="18px" toggle_font_size_phone="16px" toggle_font_size_last_edited="on|tablet" theme_builder_area="post_content" open="off"]

If you are temporarily unable to care for your loved one with memory loss, we offer Short-Term Stays as a reliable solution. Reach out to our team today to apply for your loved one’s Short-Term Stay in Memory Care.

[/et_pb_accordion_item][et_pb_accordion_item title="Does medicare cover Respite Care for dementia? " _builder_version="4.19.5" _module_preset="default" body_link_font="||||on||||" body_link_text_color="#212e65" global_colors_info="{}" toggle_text_color="#212d65" toggle_level="h2" toggle_font="Cormorant Garamond|700|||||||" toggle_font_size_tablet="18px" toggle_font_size_phone="16px" toggle_font_size_last_edited="on|tablet" theme_builder_area="post_content" open="off"]

If outside services (such as rehabilitation) are needed during a resident’s Short-Term Stay in Memory Care, Medicare coverage would be available to qualifying patients.

[/et_pb_accordion_item][/et_pb_accordion][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][/et_pb_section]
